## Source Layout

```
src/
├── main.py               Entry point
├── configs/config.py     All settings — load env vars here, never hardcode
├── dependencies.py       Dependency injection (FastAPI Depends)
{% if profile in ["rag", "full"] %}
├── ingestion/            loader → chunker → cleaner
├── embedding/            embedder wraps the embedding model
├── vectorstore/          client / indexer / retriever for {{ vector_db }}
├── rag/                  pipeline → prompt → generator (end-to-end RAG)
├── evaluation/           metrics and evaluator
{% endif %}
{% if profile in ["agent", "full"] %}
├── agents/               base_agent, chat, planner, executor
├── tools/                web_search, calculator, db_tool, rag_tool
├── llm/                  client, prompts, output_parser
├── memory/               short_term, long_term, episodic
├── workflows/            agent_loop (ReAct), planner_executor, multi_agent
├── retrieval/            RAG subsystem used by agents
├── evaluation/           agent_eval, benchmark datasets
├── guardrails/           validators and content filters
{% endif %}
├── api/                  routes, schemas, controllers
├── cache/                Redis semantic cache
├── monitoring/           tracing (OpenTelemetry) and Prometheus metrics
└── utils/                logger, helpers
```

## Key Conventions

- Config lives in `src/configs/config.py` — use `Settings` (pydantic-settings). Never hardcode keys.
- All I/O-bound functions must be `async def`.
- Use `src/utils/logger.py` for logging — no bare `print()` in production paths.
- Tests live in `tests/` — run with `uv run pytest`.
- `scripts/` contains one-off CLI scripts, not importable modules.

## Running Locally

```bash
cp .env.example .env
uv sync
uvicorn src.main:app --reload
```
